  "body": "**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Deviation from expected behavior:**\r\nChanging the cluster CRD doesn't cause changes to the cluster with error:\r\n\r\n```\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:45.693175 I | op-osd: checking if any nodes were removed\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:45.768366 I | op-osd: adding node k8s-nvme-01.sdsc.optiputer.net to the removed nodes list\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:45.768384 I | op-osd: processing 1 removed nodes\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:45.768387 I | op-osd: processing removed node k8s-nvme-01.sdsc.optiputer.net\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:45.768540 I | exec: Running command: ceph status --cluster=rook --conf=/var/lib/rook/rook/rook.config --keyring=/var/lib/rook/rook/client.admin.keyring --format json --out-file /tmp/679034901\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:45.983434 W | op-osd: skipping the removal of node k8s-nvme-01.sdsc.optiputer.net because it is not safe to do so: cluster is not fully clean. PGs: [{StateName:active+clean Count:7664} {StateName:active+clean+scrubbing+deep Count:4}]\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:45.983449 I | op-osd: done processing removed nodes\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:45.983453 I | op-osd: completed running osds in namespace rook\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:45.983530 I | exec: Running command: ceph osd unset noscrub --cluster=rook --conf=/var/lib/rook/rook/rook.config --keyring=/var/lib/rook/rook/client.admin.keyring --format json --out-file /tmp/067942512\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:47.396518 I | exec: noscrub is unset\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:47.396736 I | exec: Running command: ceph osd unset nodeep-scrub --cluster=rook --conf=/var/lib/rook/rook/rook.config --keyring=/var/lib/rook/rook/client.admin.keyring --format json --out-file /tmp/448354575\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:48.584484 I | exec: nodeep-scrub is unset\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:48.584629 I | op-cluster: Done creating rook instance in namespace rook\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:48.606419 I | op-cluster: succeeded updating cluster in namespace rook\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:48.606597 I | op-cluster: update event for cluster rook\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:48.606765 I | op-cluster: update event for cluster rook is not supported\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:48.615387 I | op-cluster: update event for cluster rook\r\n2018-10-25 19:05:48.615556 I | op-cluster: update event for cluster rook is not supported\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nScrub is disabled before making changes\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\nTry to make changes in provisioned cluster.\r\nManually setting noscrub and nodeep-scrub doesn't help since operator is setting it back just before trying to delete a node\r\n\r\nRook version (use rook version inside of a Rook Pod):\r\n0.8.2\r\nKubernetes version (use kubectl version):\r\n1.11.3\r\nKubernetes cluster type (e.g. Tectonic, GKE, OpenShift):\r\nkubeadm",
